# Flatten database schemas

User asks to **flatten** (squash, reset) **`.faproject`** schema versions/migrations during pre-release dev:

1. Invoke [fantasia-flatten-database-schemas skill](../skills/fantasia-flatten-database-schemas/SKILL.md); follow checklist end to end.
2. Merge all table DDL into **`applyFaProjectProjectDataSchemaV1`** + **`applyFaProjectContentSchemaV1`** in **`faProjectDbSchemaDdl.ts`**; remove superseded **`applyFaProjectContentSchemaV*`** / incremental migration helpers.
3. Set **`FA_PROJECT_USER_VERSION_SUPPORTED_MAX`** to new single version (**1** today); simplify **`applyFaProjectMigrations`** to bootstrap-from-zero + no-op at max only.
4. Update **`docs/database/projectDB.md`**, migration tests, user-facing changelog when flatten ships product-visible behavior (e.g. dev files must be recreated).
5. Resume normal **vN→vN+1** migration steps only when adding **next** schema change after flatten — do not restore obsolete historical ladders.

**Agents:** mention [fantasia-flatten-database-schemas](../skills/fantasia-flatten-database-schemas/SKILL.md) in **AGENTS.md** + **README.md** when documenting this capability.
